text: An earthquake measuring 4. 6 rattled Sonoma and Lake counties early Thursday, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.  The quake occurred at 2 : 09 a. m., about 14 miles northeast of Healdsburg, on the Maacama Fault with a depth of 12 miles.  A Sonoma County Sheriff's dispatcher said around 7 a. m. that there had been no reports of damage or injuries.
title: 4. 6 quake rattles Sonoma County early Thursday.
